  <page>
    <p>Each element has an associated effect and shape.  For example, Fire causes Flames, in the shape of a Sphere around caster.</p>
    <p>Spells take on the effect of the first element of the sequence. Subsequent elements of the same type will increase the power.</p>
    <p>The shape of the spell will depend on the last element in the sequence.</p>
